<reg_short_dscr>:
This register causes the DWC_trng to execute one of a number of actions. There are 3 commands available (in addition to 0, or NOP).
A write of 1 to the CMD field causes the DWC_trng to generate a new random number. The length of the random number depends on the build-time configuration setting for 'Maximum length of PRNG data' (see BUILD_CONFIG.MAX_PRNG_LEN for more details) and the MODE.MODE_R256 bit, if present. If BUILD_CONFIG.MAX_PRNG_LEN is 0, or BUILD_CONFIG.MAX_PRNG_LEN is 1 and MODE.MODE_R256 is 0, the random number will be 128 bits in length and will be available in registers RAND0 through RAND3. If BUILD_CONFIG.MAX_PRNG_LEN is 1 and MODE.MODE_R256 is 1, the random number will be 128 bits in length and will be available in registers RAND0 through RAND7. (The MODE register does not exist if BUILD_CONFIG.MAX_PRNG_LEN is 0.) This operation is only valid if the PRNG portion of the core has been previously seeded (see STAT.SEEDED bit description for more details).
A write of 2 to the CMD field causes the DWC_trng to generate and load a new random seed from the ring oscillator-based seed generator.
A write of 3 to the CMD field causes the DWC_trng to load a nonce from the SEEDx registers. This command is only valid if the DWC_trng is currently in NONCE mode (see SMODE.SMODE_NONCE_MODE bit description for more details).
