<reg_short_dscr>:
The NONCE_MODE field indicates that the engine is currently waiting for the host to load a nonce through the SEEDx registers. In this mode, the host completes the nonce load operation by writing a CMD_NONCE_RESEED command (3) to the CTRL.CMD field. The CMD_NONCE_RESEED command is ignored if NONCE_MODE is not set.
The R256 field indicates if the PRNG is configured to collect 128-bit or 256-bit values. This bit reflects the state of the MODE.MODE_R256 mode bit.
The MISSION_MODE field indicates if the PRNG is set to mission mode or test mode. This bit reflects the state of the SMODE.SMODE_MISSION_MODE mode bit.
The SEEDED field indicates that the PRNG portion of the DWC_trng is currently in a seeded state. The source of the seed is saved to the LAST_RESEED field. If the SMODE.SECURE_EN field is changed (that is, 1 to 0 or 0 to 1) or the I_zeroize> port is driven to 1 (if available), the internal state of the DWC_trng is erased (zeroized) and the SEEDED field is cleared. When SEEDED is 0 it indicates that the DWC_trng must be (re)seed to before it can generate random numbers.
The LAST_RESEED field indicates what type of operation created the current seed.
The SRVC_RQST field reflects the fact that one or more of the ISTAT fields are asserted.
The RAND_RESEEDING and RAND_GENERATING fields indicate that the DWC_trng is currently executing one or more of these 2 tasks.
