<reg_short_dscr>:
This register is used to set the length of the PRNG output register.
The R256 bit allows the DWC_trng to be configured for collection of 128- or 256-bit data from the PRNG.
When R256 is set to 1, the DWC_trng collects 256 bits of data in the RANDx registers before asserting the ISTAT.RAND_RDY bit. The collected data is available in RAND0 through RAND7.
When R256 is set to 0, the DWC_trng collects 128 bits of data in the RANDx registers before asserting the ISTAT.RAND_RDY bit. The collected data is available in RAND0 through RAND3. Registers RAND4 through RAND7 are unused and read back as 0 in 128-bit mode.
