<reg_short_dscr>:
This register is used to enable or disable interrupts within the DWC_trng. When both one of the individual enable bits and GLBL_EN bit are set to 1, an occurrence of that event drives the O_irq port to 1.
The RAND_RDY_EN bit enables the contribution from the random number ready logic (ISTAT.RAND_RDY).
The SEED_DONE_EN bit enables the contribution from the seed completion logic (ISTAT.SEED_DONE).
The RQST_ALARM_EN bit enables RQST reminder alarm (ISTAT.RQST_ALARM).
The AGE_ALARM_EN bit enables AGE_ALARM_ENAGE reminder alarm (ISTAT.AGE_ALARM).
The LFSR_LOCKUP_EN bit enables the contribution from the LFSR lockup logic (ISTAT.LFSR_LOCKUP).
The GLBL_EN bit is the global interrupt enable signal for the DWC_trng. Setting this bit to 0 disables all interrupts. Setting this bit to 1 allows any of the individually enabled interrupt sources to generate an interrupt through the O_irq port.
NOTE: These bits are not cleared to their reset state in a zeroize event. They retain their state.
