<reg_short_dscr>:
The RAND0 register is part of the RANDx register set which are used by the host to read the newly generated random number.
There is no endian-ness to the data in the RANDx registers because they are random. Therefore, it does not matter if software uses RAND0 as the least significant or most significant word for the collected random number. Nor does it matter if bit 0 or bit 31 of each individual register is used at the least or most significant bit.
