<reg_short_dscr>:
The SEED0 register is part of the SEEDx register set which are used to load a host generated nonce seed into the DWC_trng. These registers are also used in several test modes to access internal data.
The specific operation of these registers depends on several mode bits and build-time parameter settings.
- When in MISSION_MODE mode and not in NONCE mode, writes to these registers result have no effect and reads return 0.
- When in MISSION_MODE mode and NONCE mode, the writes the user-defined seed to these registers. The seed is loaded into the DWC_trng when a CMD_NONCE_RESEED command (3) is next written toCTRL.CMD register field. Reading these registers returns the currently loaded seed.
- When in TEST_MODE mode, these register can be both written and read regardless of the state of the SMODE.SMODE_NONCE_MODE register. A read after a random reseed operation returns the seed which was generated by the random seed generator.
NOTE: The following applies to all the SEEDx registers.
When in MISSION_MODE mode and SMODE.SMODE_NONCE_MODE is 0, the SEEDx registers return 0 when read, and writes have no effect.
When in MISSION_MODE mode and SMODE.SMODE_NONCE_MODE is 1, the SEEDx registers are used to inject a 255-bit seed into the DWC_trng. The actual seeding event is only executed when in NONCE mode and a 2 is written to the CTRL.CMD register.
NOTE: The change into NONCE mode is detected by internal circuitry and used to scrub the previous contents of the seed register. Thus, the previous random seed is not leaked when switching to NONCE mode while in MISSION_MODE.
