NOTE: The SEED7.SEED7_SEED field is 32 bits wide but the most significant bit of this register is not used by the DWC_trng for seed purposes. When manually seeding the core in NONCE mode, this bit is DONT_CARE when written and is considered undefined when read. However, when SMODE.SMODE_MISSION_MODE is set to 0 (TEST_MODE), the full 256-bit random seed generated by a CMD_RAND_RESEED command deposits a fully random bit in this location. This feature can be used if random seed qualification analysis is performed against the core. This bit is masked off when the random seed is injected into the PRNG portion of the core.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Seed data word 7.
