<reg_short_dscr>:
This register allows the DWC_trng to generate a reseed reminder alarm after a specified number of random numbers have been requested by the host. If the RQSTS field holds a value of 0, this feature is disabled and no AUTO_RQSTS alarms are generated.
The feature operates in a watchdog-like fashion with the internal counter being reloaded from the RQSTS register field whenever the counter reaches 0. The internal counter is decremented once for every 16 host random number requests (that is, whenever CTRL.CMD is written with a 1, or CMD_GEN_RAND). When the internal counter reaches 0 and the RQSTS field is not 0, a reseed reminder alarm is triggered.
Whenever a reseed event (of any type) is executed, the internal counter is automatically reloaded from this register.
If 'Enable auto-reseed loopback mode' was selected at build-time (see BUILD_CONFIG.AUTO_RESEED_LOOPBACK bit for more details), this alarm autonomously executes the equivalent of a CMD_RAND_RESEED command (see CTRL register for more details) and refreshes the PRNG portion of the core with a newly generated random seed.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
0 = disable the AUTO_RQSTS alarm feature
other = reload value for internal AUTO_RQSTS counter
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
This register allows the DWC_trng to generate a reseed reminder alarm after a specified number of random numbers have been requested by the host. If the AGE field holds a value of 0, this feature is disabled and no AUTO_AGE alarms are generated.
The feature operates in a watchdog-like fashion with internal counter being reloaded from the AGE register field whenever the counter reaches 0. The internal counter is decremented once every 67.1 million (that is, 2**26) clock cycles. When the internal counter reaches 0 and the AGE field is not 0, a reseed reminder alarm is triggered.
Whenever a reseed event (of any type) is executed, the internal counter is automatically reloaded from this register.
If 'Enable auto-reseed loopback mode' was selected at build-time (see BUILD_CONFIG.AUTO_RESEED_LOOPBACK bit for more details), this alarm autonomously executes the equivalent of a CMD_RAND_RESEED command (see CTRL register for more details) and refreshes the PRNG portion of the core with a newly generated random seed.
------------------------------
